   all  about getElementById 
{ it can selects in only one element
 it retuns Element
 its not live and  its also not uses css  selector}






all about getElementByClassName{
    it  can  selects   in multiple element
    and  it return htmlcullection
    and its live
    and its not  uses  for css  selector as like getElementById
}

all about querySelector {

it can selects only one element (first matching element)

it returns Element

it is not live

it us CSS selector

 # for id
 . for class

it can select by tag name (div, p, etc.)

it can select by attribute (input[type="text"])
}

all about querySelectorAll {

it can selects multiple elements

it returns NodeList

it is not live (static)

it uses CSS selector

we  use # for id

we  use . for class

it can select by tag, class, id, attribute

it supports forEach() method directly
}




               